{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"226fb14e-dba8-484b-b326-1a04dedceb6f","content":"Use `dotnet watch test` — it re-runs tests automatically whenever you save a file:\n\n```\ndotnet watch test --filter \"RemoveStock_ExceedsAvailable_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThe `--filter` flag scopes it to just that one test. Every time you save `InventoryServiceTests.cs`, it will rebuild and re-run.\n\n**Why the test fails:** `RemoveStock` never throws — it just subtracts into negative values. You'll need to add a guard like:\n\n```csharp\npublic void RemoveStock(string sku, int quantity)\n{\n    var current = _stock.GetValueOrDefault(sku);\n    if (quantity > current)\n        throw new InvalidOperationException(\"Insufficient stock\");\n    _stock[sku] = current - quantity;\n}\n```\n\nWant me to apply that fix and start the watch loop?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"79c94c58-d706-4452-bc71-f664a8f9391f","outputTokens":209},"id":"528f1eb5-74c2-495f-9195-c98c0e6858a2","timestamp":"2026-04-07T13:04:49.624Z","parentId":"9944cb6b-d2c8-474c-9abe-14467a49a5e1"}
